content: And the product suppliers to these companies needing to be close to their major clients, continue to absorb additional industrial space as they all benefit from the skills and availability of labor pools lower energy costs, excellent infrastructure and transportation, lower taxes and government incentives, friendly regulatory pro business environments and quality of life and cost of living benefits, and our recent Chief Executive International Economic Development Council survey, 38% of the CEOs, mostly of mid-market manufacturers responded that they are primarily focused on relocating or expanding to the Midwest, 33% indicated the Southeast.
